PROFESSOR: Recap last night
and give you-- remember

00:00:23.720 --> 00:00:26.010
what we had for an overview.

00:00:26.010 --> 00:00:32.640
The first part was that it's
not about the business plan,

00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:34.040
it's about planning.

00:00:34.040 --> 00:00:36.960
That was the first
point I hope you got.

00:00:36.960 --> 00:00:41.540
The second one is that planning
is not a static process.

00:00:41.540 --> 00:00:43.010
It's dynamic.

00:00:43.010 --> 00:00:45.520
And therefore, your plan
is going to be dynamic.

00:00:45.520 --> 00:00:49.180
However you write it
down, or put it in slides.

00:00:49.180 --> 00:00:51.870
That's the first set of points.

00:00:51.870 --> 00:00:56.240
The second is the
three Ys-- or sorry,

00:00:56.240 --> 00:01:00.000
the second is your goals and
tasks in this whole process.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.630
It's to create value.

00:01:02.630 --> 00:01:06.400
And the second goal is to
harvest some of the value.

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:09.800
And as we pointed out,
those are easy to say

00:01:09.800 --> 00:01:12.160
and it's increasingly
hard to do.

00:01:12.160 --> 00:01:13.910
The rest of the course
will be telling you

00:01:13.910 --> 00:01:16.820
try to how to do those things.

00:01:16.820 --> 00:01:20.150
The questions that investors
are going to be asking

00:01:20.150 --> 00:01:22.190
are the 3 Whys.

00:01:22.190 --> 00:01:22.860
Why this?

00:01:22.860 --> 00:01:25.380
Why is this something important?

00:01:25.380 --> 00:01:26.400
Why now?

00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:28.920
Why is now the
right time to do it?

00:01:28.920 --> 00:01:30.190
And why this team?

00:01:30.190 --> 00:01:32.895
Why is this group of
people the right people?

00:01:32.895 --> 00:01:34.770
And if they get through
those, the fourth one

00:01:34.770 --> 00:01:37.610
is why won't it work?

00:01:37.610 --> 00:01:40.400
Now, I said that that's
what investors ask,

00:01:40.400 --> 00:01:42.620
and that's probably what
you ought to be asking.

00:01:42.620 --> 00:01:45.800
Because the final point is,
the most scarce resource is not

00:01:45.800 --> 00:01:48.240
money, it's your time.

00:01:48.240 --> 00:01:50.050
So if you're not happy
with those answers

00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:51.880
to those questions,
then you ought

00:01:51.880 --> 00:01:55.980
to iterate and find some new
questions-- a new approach

00:01:55.980 --> 00:01:56.480
to those.

00:01:56.480 --> 00:01:59.330
In fact, tonight our
speaker Bob is probably

00:01:59.330 --> 00:02:02.040
going to talk about how you've
iterated [INAUDIBLE] things

00:02:02.040 --> 00:02:02.980
on that score.

00:02:02.980 --> 00:02:05.670
OK, so tonight
we're starting down

00:02:05.670 --> 00:02:08.039
the path of filling
in the business plan.

00:02:08.039 --> 00:02:11.160
The first thing we said if
you've got to create value.

00:02:11.160 --> 00:02:12.970
And one of the ways
you can create value

00:02:12.970 --> 00:02:14.980
is to find a customer.

00:02:14.980 --> 00:02:18.920
And Bob Jones, who's one of
our highly paid volunteers,

00:02:18.920 --> 00:02:22.990
once again tripling your income.

00:02:22.990 --> 00:02:26.554
Bob is-- was a classmate
of mine at Sloan.

00:02:26.554 --> 00:02:27.970
People in the
audience from Sloan,

00:02:27.970 --> 00:02:30.530
do you know about
the C-function?

00:02:30.530 --> 00:02:31.230
Still going on?

00:02:31.230 --> 00:02:32.940
You like that?

00:02:32.940 --> 00:02:33.510
That's Bob.

00:02:33.510 --> 00:02:36.790
He's the guy that organized
the first C-function.

00:02:36.790 --> 00:02:44.360
In addition to being a serial
entrepreneur-- for those of you

00:02:44.360 --> 00:02:46.650
who are not from the
Sloan side of campus,

00:02:46.650 --> 00:02:50.410
the C-Function is consumption
function in economics.

00:02:50.410 --> 00:02:54.130
And you can picture what might
be consumed at a Friday night

00:02:54.130 --> 00:02:55.390
consumption function.

00:02:55.390 --> 00:02:57.110
So we'll leave it with that.

00:02:57.110 --> 00:02:59.480
Bob's a serial
entrepreneur, still at it.

00:02:59.480 --> 00:03:01.900
Like a lot of the speakers
that we're going to hear from,

00:03:01.900 --> 00:03:04.550
they're actually
doing the very things

00:03:04.550 --> 00:03:06.150
they're talking to you about.

00:03:06.150 --> 00:03:09.690
So this isn't just an
academic exercise for them.

00:03:09.690 --> 00:03:14.680
Bob's other claim to fame is he
plays pretty good blues guitar

00:03:14.680 --> 00:03:16.190
and he has a blues band.

00:03:16.190 --> 00:03:17.710
But I'll let him
decide whether he

00:03:17.710 --> 00:03:20.090
wants to say anything
more about that.

00:03:20.090 --> 00:03:23.620
And with that, Bob, the
clicker is yours, sir.

00:03:23.620 --> 00:03:26.330
BOB JONES: Thanks, Joe.

00:03:26.330 --> 00:03:28.212
So good evening, everybody.

00:03:28.212 --> 00:03:32.090
I'd like to congratulate you
on the good sense required

00:03:32.090 --> 00:03:34.570
to sign up for one
of the best courses

00:03:34.570 --> 00:03:37.170
that the Institute offers.

00:03:37.170 --> 00:03:39.090
It's not the first
course here you'll

00:03:39.090 --> 00:03:42.410
take here that has you
drinking from a fire hose.

00:03:42.410 --> 00:03:45.360
But this one's pretty
valuable stuff.

00:03:45.360 --> 00:03:48.450
How many of you are
in this because you're

00:03:48.450 --> 00:03:51.115
thinking of competing
in the 100K competition?

00:03:54.020 --> 00:03:55.310
Good.

00:03:55.310 --> 00:03:59.390
How many of you
are contemplating

00:03:59.390 --> 00:04:01.500
making your living
in entrepreneurship

00:04:01.500 --> 00:04:04.130
when you get out of here?

00:04:04.130 --> 00:04:07.480
Oh dear, you poor things.

00:04:07.480 --> 00:04:12.540
How many of you actually have
something going right now?

00:04:12.540 --> 00:04:13.700
Wow.

00:04:13.700 --> 00:04:18.339
Well there's therapy available
for you guys, and medication.

00:04:18.339 --> 00:04:21.120
This is a little bit
like chronic illness,

00:04:21.120 --> 00:04:23.410
you might be able to
tamp it down for a while

00:04:23.410 --> 00:04:25.374
and then it'll pop up again.

00:04:25.374 --> 00:04:26.790
You won't be able
to get rid of it

00:04:26.790 --> 00:04:29.750
once you're infected
and afflicted.

00:04:29.750 --> 00:04:32.950
I'd love some sense of what
you guys are working on,

00:04:32.950 --> 00:04:36.520
just some sense of the spectrum
of who's doing what here.

00:04:36.520 --> 00:04:38.700
Do you have a dog
walking service

00:04:38.700 --> 00:04:42.020
for two-income
families, or do you

00:04:42.020 --> 00:04:45.950
have something that detects
the need for insulin

00:04:45.950 --> 00:04:47.396
in a patient with diabetes?

00:04:47.396 --> 00:04:49.020
So somebody raise
your hand and give me

00:04:49.020 --> 00:04:52.380
some sense of what it is
you're working on, please.

00:04:52.380 --> 00:04:52.880
Yes, sir.

00:04:53.832 --> 00:04:56.886
AUDIENCE: Business systems
for small- and medium-sized

00:04:56.886 --> 00:04:58.385
BOB JONES: I'm
sorry, business what?

